Class Airplane

java.lang.Object
Inheritance.Transportation
Inheritance.Aircraft
Inheritance.Airplane
public class Airplane extends Aircraft
The Airplane class is a subclass of Aircraft. The Airplane class describes an fixed-wing aircraft that is propelled forward by thrust through engines.

      public Airplane(String name, double fuel, double avgSpeed, double altitute, double wingspan, double thrust, double chordLen)
      Constructs a Aircraft object with the given parameters
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the transportation system
      avgSpeed - the average speed of the system, in m/s
      altitute - the current altitute the aircraft is at, in m
      wingspan - the wingspan(length from one wing to the other) of the airplane, in m
      thrust - the thrust force of the engines, in lb
      chordLen - the chord length, in m
      amountOfFuel - the amount of fuel remaining in the system, in L
